Why Privacy? Why Now?
We live in an era of mass data collection. Every click, every purchase, every interaction is tracked, stored, and monetized. Traditional blockchains made this worse ‚Äî putting financial and behavioral data on permanent public display.

Zero-knowledge cryptography changes everything.

The Aleo Advantage
Offchain Execution ‚Äî Compute privately, verify publicly
Encrypted State ‚Äî Data hidden by default
Private, but Compliant ‚Äî Meet regulatory requirements through selective disclosure
Composability ‚Äî Private contracts can interact seamlessly
Backed by a16z, SoftBank, and Samsung, Aleo is the infrastructure layer for the private internet.

The question is: What will you build when privacy is the default?

